Let's use Hint 1 and Hint 2 to derive Equation 1. The difference in the x-coordinates of any point P and F1 is $|PF_1|$. Similarly, the difference in the x-coordinates of any point P and F2 is $|PF_2|$. Using the Pythagorean theorem, the distance between any two points (P,F1), and (P,F2) is given by $|PF_1 - PF_2| = \sqrt{(x_{F_1}-x_{F_2})^2+(y_{F_1}-y_{F_2})^2}$. Substituting the given x and y coordinates in this formula and equating it to 24, we get:

\begin{align*}
|PF_1 - PF_2| &= 24 \\
\sqrt{(x_{P} - 10)^2 + (y_{P} - 2)^2-\left(\sqrt{(x_{P} + 16)^2 + (y_{P} - 2)^2}\right)|} &= 24
\end{align*}
